            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Absolutely agree. I think as a first step, the marker fold method would be the highest level fold. For the following code block, each of the functions could fold on their own (as well as other syntax folding within each function) but the marker fold would collapse all three.\r\n\r\n```c\r\n// {{{\r\nint func1(int x) {\r\n\r\n}\r\nint func2(int x) {\r\n\r\n}\r\nint func3(int x) {\r\n\r\n}\r\n// }}}\r\n```\r\n\r\nLong term, it would be nice if the two fold methods could interact with each other.\r\n\r\n```c\r\n\r\nint func1(int x) {\r\n    \\\\{{{ coplicated code block\r\n\r\n    \\\\}}}\r\n\r\n    \\\\{{{ other coplicated code block\r\n    \r\n    while (some_condition) {\r\n        // operation\r\n    }\r\n    \\\\}}}\r\n\r\n    while (new_condition) {\r\n        // operation\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```",
